component Resource Efficiency [0.45, 0.50] label [5, -10]

// --- Dependencies: consumer-facing ---
Consumer -> Sustainable Product
Consumer -> Sustainability Rating / Label
Consumer -> Retailer

Retailer -> Online Distribution
Retailer -> Storefront Distribution
Retailer -> Cooperative Distribution
Retailer -> Certification Scheme
Retailer -> Producer

Sustainable Product -> Producer
Sustainable Product -> Packaging
Sustainable Product -> Certification Scheme

Sustainability Rating / Label -> Certification Scheme
Sustainability Rating / Label -> Disclosure Reporting
Sustainability Rating / Label -> Audit

// --- Producer side ---
Producer -> Manufacturing
Producer -> Raw Material Sourcing
Producer -> Complex Product Sourcing
Producer -> Packaging
Producer -> Temperature / Freshness Handling
Producer -> Last-Mile Transportation
Producer -> Backhaul Transportation
Producer -> Resource Efficiency
Producer -> Waste Handling

Manufacturing -> Raw Material Sourcing
Manufacturing -> Complex Product Sourcing
Manufacturing -> Resource Efficiency

Last-Mile Transportation -> Backhaul Transportation
Online Distribution -> Last-Mile Transportation
Storefront Distribution -> Backhaul Transportation
Cooperative Distribution -> Last-Mile Transportation

Packaging -> Raw Material Sourcing
Temperature / Freshness Handling -> Backhaul Transportation

Waste Handling -> Reusability / Circular Return
Reusability / Circular Return -> Sustainability R&D
Resource Efficiency -> Sustainability R&D

// --- Regulator side ---
Regulator -> Laws and Regulations
Regulator -> Trade Agreements
Regulator -> Sanctions
Regulator -> Regulatory Guidelines
Regulator -> Bureaucracy
Regulator -> Monitoring

Laws and Regulations -> Bureaucracy
Trade Agreements -> Bureaucracy
Sanctions -> Bureaucracy
Regulatory Guidelines -> Bureaucracy

// --- Compliance binds producer to regulator ---
Producer -> Laws and Regulations
Producer -> Trade Agreements
Producer -> Sanctions
Producer -> Regulatory Guidelines
Producer -> Disclosure Reporting
Producer -> Monitoring
Producer -> Audit

Audit -> Monitoring
Disclosure Reporting -> Monitoring
Certification Scheme -> Audit
Certification Scheme -> Regulatory Guidelines

// --- Movement (evolution arrows) ---
evolve Sustainability Rating / Label 0.92
evolve Certification Scheme 0.78
evolve Disclosure Reporting 0.72
evolve Audit 0.76
evolve Monitoring 0.70
evolve Resource Efficiency 0.62
evolve Reusability / Circular Return 0.60
evolve Sustainability R&D 0.35
evolve Regulatory Guidelines 0.58
evolve Temperature / Freshness Handling 0.70
evolve Complex Product Sourcing 0.62

// --- Inertia markers ---
// Bureaucracy x — resistant to modernisation
// Storefront Distribution x — legacy retail footprint
// Cooperative Distribution x — community inertia

// --- Annotations ---
annotation 1 [[0.15, 0.37]] Sustainability R&D: Genesis-leaning, where novel materials and circular models emerge
annotation 2 [[0.82, 0.80]] Consumer-visible ratings are commoditising; labels aggregate upstream compliance signals
annotation 3 [[0.50, 0.83]] Regulatory pressure concentrated here — law + trade + bureaucracy cluster pushes producer rightward
annotations [0.02, 0.02]

